Uses of Interface
com.ikalagaming.packages.Package

  • Packages that use Package 
    Package Description
    com.ikalagaming.gui.console
    A console for interfacing with the engine, and associated classes.
    com.ikalagaming.packages
    Manages packages, which are distinct subsystems of the engine that can be dynamically swapped in and out or enabled/disabled during runtime.
    com.ikalagaming.packages.events
    Events dispatched by the package system.
    com.ikalagaming.packages.rng
    A simple random number generator package that should be fairly secure.
    com.ikalagaming.system
    Provides ways of communicating with and controlling the core of the engine (event manager, package manager) using events.

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean PackageManager.disable(Package target)
      Deactivates the package and halts all of its operations.
      boolean PackageManager.enable(Package target)
      Activates the package and enables it to perform its normal functions.
      PackageState PackageManager.getPackageState(Package target)
      Returns the current state of the package.
      boolean PackageManager.isEnabled(Package target)
      Returns true if the package is enabled, and false otherwise.
      boolean PackageManager.isLoaded(Package type)
      Returns true if a package exists that has the same type as the provided package (for example: "Graphics").
      boolean PackageManager.loadPackage(Package toLoad)
      Loads the given package into memory, stores it by type, and enables it if packages are enabled on load by default.

      Attempts to register the command for the given class.
      boolean PackageManager.reload(Package target)

      Attempts to unload the package from memory.
      void PackageManager.unregisterPackageCommands(Package owner)
